    • disablePaymentChannels

      public DisablePaymentChannelsResults disablePaymentChannels(String id, DisablePaymentChannels disablePaymentChannels) throws ApiException
      Disables one or more payment channels associated with a token in the India market. Applicable to the India market only, this API is used to disable specific payment channels for a token. A transaction submitted with a POS Entry mode for a disabled channel will be declined. If disabledPaymentChannels are provided the current list of disabled channels will be returned.
      Parameters:
      id - Static endpoint iteration number (Not API Version) (required)
      disablePaymentChannels - JSON object containing parameters Disable selected payment channels (required)
      Returns:
      DisablePaymentChannelsResults
      Throws:
      ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
      Http Response Details:
      Status Code Description Response Headers
      200 Disable Payment Channels Response -
